getLastViewedByMeDate().Description: Returns the date which will be recorded as when the user most recently viewed the resource or null if unchanged.

getCustomPropertyChangeMap().Description: Returns a map that defines the custom property changes for the resource. The map is from the property keys to the new or updated values. Null values correspond to properties that are going to be deleted.

getTitle().Description: Returns the new title for the resource or null if unchanged.

isPinned().Description: Returns the new pinned state for the resource or null if unchanged.

isViewed().Description: Returns the new viewed state for the resource or null if unchanged.

getIndexableText().Description: Returns the new text to be indexed for the resource or null if unchanged.

getMimeType().Description: Returns the new MIME type for the resource or null if unchanged.

isStarred().Description: Returns the new starred state for the resource or null if unchanged.

getDescription().Description: Returns the new description for the resource or null if unchanged.

ClassDesc: A collection of metadata changes. Any fields with null values will retain their current value.
